'''Callum Bruce''' (born 9 June 1983 in [[Hastings, New Zealand]]) is a New Zealand [[rugby union]] player.

==Super 14==
Bruce formerly played for the [[Super Rugby]] team [[Highlanders (Super rugby franchise)|Highlanders]]. He played for the [[Super Rugby]] team [[Chiefs (Super rugby franchise)|Chiefs]]. Although his normal position is [[Centre (rugby union)|second five-eighth]], Bruce has also covered [[Rugby_union_positions#10._Fly-half|first five-eighth]] for the Highlanders when regular fly-half [[Nick Evans (rugby union)|Nick Evans]] has been injured. 

In June 2010 it was announced that Callum would be moving to play in Japan.

